Practical 12: NotebookLM Project

Aim

To create revision notes using NotebookLM.

Objectives
	•	To generate study guide
	•	To create flashcards

Materials Required
	•	NotebookLM

Procedure
	
1. Create NotebookLM project – Start a new project in NotebookLM to organize your materials and AI-generated outputs in one workspace.


2. Upload two resources – Add two documents or sources to the project so the AI can analyze and reference them.


3. Generate study guide – Use NotebookLM’s tools to create a structured study guide summarizing key concepts from the uploaded resources.


4. Generate flashcards – Automatically produce flashcards that highlight important facts, terms, or ideas for easier review.


5. Review accuracy – Carefully check the summaries and flashcards to 5.  ensure all information is correct and reflects the original resources.


6. Take screenshots – Capture screenshots of the study guide and flashcards to document your work or include them in your submission

ANSWERS -
Aim:

To create revision notes using NotebookLM.

Objectives:

To generate a structured study guide.

To create flashcards for quick revision.

Materials Required:

NotebookLM (Google AI tool)

Procedure (Answer):

1.Create a NotebookLM project:
Open NotebookLM and start a new project to organize all study materials and AI-generated notes.

2.Upload two resources:
Add two documents, PDFs, or text sources so the AI can read and analyze them.

3.Generate a study guide:
Use NotebookLM’s “Study Guide” feature to create summarized notes covering key points, definitions, and explanations from the uploaded materials.

4.Generate flashcards:
Use the AI flashcard feature to automatically create important questions and answers for revision.

5.Review accuracy:
Read the generated study guide and flashcards carefully to ensure the information matches the original documents and is factually correct.

6.Take screenshots:
Capture screenshots of the study guide and flashcards to include in your practical file or to show proof of work.

Observation (Answer):

NotebookLM successfully created:

1.A clear and organized study guide from uploaded documents.

2.Flashcards containing key terms and important questions.
Minor edits were required to correct small errors and improve clarity.

Result:

A complete study guide and a set of accurate flashcards were generated using NotebookLM, which can be used for exam revision.

Conclusion:

NotebookLM makes revision easier by converting long documents into concise notes and flashcards. This helps students save time and study more effectively.
